# Pyramid — square-base right pyramid, 1×1×1, centered horizontally.
# Square base sits at y=-0.5 (the only valid attachment face); apex
# at y=+0.5. All four side faces are isosceles triangles.
#
# Vertex layout:
#   v1 = back-bottom-left   (-, -, -)
#   v2 = back-bottom-right  (+, -, -)
#   v3 = front-bottom-right (+, -, +)
#   v4 = front-bottom-left  (-, -, +)
#   v5 = apex               ( 0, +, 0)
#
# Faces: 1 base quad + 4 side triangles.
#
# Winding: each face is wound so the right-hand-rule cross product
# of (v1→v2) × (v1→v3) points outward. In Unity's left-handed coord
# system this corresponds to clockwise screen-space winding when
# viewed from outside, so single-sided rendering shows every face.
# PyramidWeaponMat is also set to render double-sided as a safety net.

o Pyramid

v -0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5 -0.5  0.5
v -0.5 -0.5  0.5
v  0.0  0.5  0.0

# Per-face flat normals.
vn  0.0 -1.0       0.0
vn  0.0  0.4472136 0.8944272
vn  0.8944272  0.4472136  0.0
vn  0.0  0.4472136 -0.8944272
vn -0.8944272  0.4472136  0.0

# Unit-square UVs reused across faces (apex re-uses index 5).
vt 0.0 0.0
vt 1.0 0.0
vt 1.0 1.0
vt 0.0 1.0
vt 0.5 1.0

# Base quad — normal -Y. CCW from below gives outward normal.
f 1/1/1 2/2/1 3/3/1
f 1/1/1 3/3/1 4/4/1

# Front side — normal +Y +Z.
f 4/1/2 3/2/2 5/5/2

# Right side — normal +X +Y.
f 3/1/3 2/2/3 5/5/3

# Back side — normal -Z +Y.
f 2/1/4 1/2/4 5/5/4

# Left side — normal -X +Y.
f 1/1/5 4/2/5 5/5/5
